de.oaam.model.oaam.scenario

Interface OperationModeReference

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    OperationModeReferenceImpl

    public interface OperationModeReference
extends OaamBaseElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Operation Mode Reference'. This is the link between temporary objects and time frames. This allows to define a probability of the element of being active during certain time frames.

    The following features are supported:

    • Operation Mode
    • Active Probability
    See Also:
    ScenarioPackage.getOperationModeReference()

      • getActiveProbability

        double getActiveProbability()
        Returns the value of the 'Active Probability' attribute. The default value is "1.0". Ranges from 0 to 1. It is the probability that the element is active in the given operation mode. If it is active the full time frame 1 has to be specified, which is also the default value.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Active Probability' attribute.
        See Also:
        setActiveProbability(double), ScenarioPackage.getOperationModeReference_ActiveProbability()
